@node "historymcp" "History of MCP"
                                 @{b} History of MCP
                                  ==============@{ub}

The programmer: {s}:Stefan, {m}:Michael, {v}:Vincent, {o}:Soeren
This doesn't mean, that each programmer only revise your own routines!

>>USER<< is the name of the user, who reported the bug.

FIXED = fixed
ADDED = new
REMOV = removed
REWRI = rewritten
OVERW = overworked
IMPRO = improved


****************************************************************************

@{b}MCP V1.30@{ub} ---------

(16-Sep-97)

 - {m}  ADDED   note how the ChangeWorkbenchTitle should work with DOpus5.
                >> Thanks to Michal Kozusznik <<

(05-Sep-97)

 - {m}  ADDED   the new WWW-addresses to the guide.
                Special thanks to Mario Cattaneo which makes it possible!

(04-Sep-97)

 - {m}  ADDED   note for NSDPatch users to the guide. Formatprotection
                doesn't work without some changes.
                >> Thomas Klein <<

 - {m}  FIXED   small underscores feature
                >> Mario Cattaneo <<

 - {m}  FIXED   SysIHack bug.. The screen gadget colors were not correct.
                >> Sebastian Becker und Edward Niedziejko <<

(31-Aug-97)

 - {s}  FIXED   SysIHack problem. (solid window moving works now over
                WB-Palette-Prefs)
                >> Alexander Kneer <<

 - {m}  FIXED   ScreensMenu to work with PowerWindows.

(12-Aug-97)

 - {m}  FIXED   little bug in 'Execute Command'.
                >> Ian Kumlien <<

(10-Aug-97)

 - {m}  FIXED   bug in SysIHack when deactivating MCP
                >> Mario Cattaneo <<

(27-Jul-97)

 - {m}  ADDED   option for small underscores in the NewGadtools function
                >> Thanks to Mario Cattaneo for the 25DM phone call :) <<

 - {m}  ADDED   Center Screen function to the ScreenManager.

(26-Jul-97)

 - {m}  OVERW   ShapeShifter LockTask function.

(22-Jul-97)

 - {m}  ADDED   Rearrange function to SysIHack. Now MCP change the position
                of every gadget in the right border. This fixes problems
                with the greater Sizegadget. It works not with every program,
                because some of them adds the arrows or the slider after
                opening the window.

(20-Jul-97)

 - {m}  REMOV   CloseScreenPatch

(24-Jun-97)

 - {m}  FIXED   support of filterfunc in a ASL-Filerequester
                >> Thanks to Markus Hillenbrand for the demos <<

(21-Jun-97)

 - {m}  ADDED   a little function to make the mousepointer visible in the
                gap between two Amiga screens. This function will be
                installed automatically.
                >> Thanks Alexander Kühn for the source <<

(15-Jun-97)

 - {m}  IMPRO   looking of SysIHack arrows.
                >> Alexander Limi <<

(14-Jun-97)

 - {m}  FIXED   NewGadtools didn't care about the Fontstyle
                >> Davide Bigazzi, Allan Odgaard <<
                >> Thanks for the Demo from Jarda Pokorny <<

 - {m}  FIXED   wrong save place function of LockPatch and WBAbout
                >> Remigiusz Kierunczyk <<

 - {ms} REWRI   SysIHack

(12-Jun-97)

 - {m}  FIXED   forgot to unlock the Pubscreen in FreeWBPens (%wp) of
                ChangeWBTitle

 - {m}  FIXED   little bug in centering code of NewGadTools

(07-Jun-97)

 - {m}  ADDED   CloseScreen Patch
                >> source from Jens Troeger <<

(06-Jun-97)

 - {m}  FIXED   Enforcer-Hit, because Cygnus-Ed stores illegal data in the
                NewWindow-Extension field.
                >> Eric Sauvageau <<

(05-Jun-97)

 - {m}  FIXED   minimum values for sizegadgets
                >> Jens Troeger <<

 - {m}  FIXED   Enforcer-Hit with Term
                >> Torsten Bach <<

(03-Jun-97)

 - {m}  FIXED   name THEN condition to THEN assignments.
                >> Mario Cattaneo <<

(01-Jun-97)

 - {ms} ADDED   changing of Sizegadget width and height and sizing of all
                window borders.

(31-May-97)

 - {m}  FIXED   memory leak in SysIHack
                >> Christian Birchinger <<

 - {m}  REMOV   NoFrag, because it doesn't work with DynamiCache and IBrowse.
                It's no failure of NoFrag, because it only sets the
                MEMF_Reverse flag in the AllocMemory() call.

(30-May-97)

 - {m}  FIXED   little bug new in the TitleClock
                >> Christian Birchinger <<

(29-May-97)

 - {m}  FIXED   Enforcer-Hit in InsertClip
                >> Arndt van der Molen <<

 - {m}  REWRI   pattern matching in the TitleClock. Now it's faster.

(28-May-97)

 - {m}  FIXED   zero check in HiresPointer code

(27-May-97)

 - {m}  FIXED   NewGadtools centering problem. AB-Tools was trashed.
                >> Allan Odgaard <<

(25-May-97)

 - {m}  ADDED   MapUmlauts hotkey

(18-May-97)

 - {m}  FIXED   memory leak in SysIHack

 - {s}  FIXED   bad colors after reopening Workbench

 - {m}  REMOV   for the time the drag and drop option in the IF and THEN
                condition lists of the ScreenManager.
                >> Theodoropoulos Kostas <<

(15-May-97)

 - {m}  FIXED   QuickLayers check. Could crash..

(13-May-97)

 - {m}  IMPRO   QuickLayers now checks if CGFX/Superlayers function
                activated.

(08-May-97)

 - {m}  ADDED   FreeWBPens option to ChangeWBTitle function. It shows the
                free pens.

(24-Apr-97)

 - {m}  FIXED   Enforcer-Hits with NoIconBorder and Merlin-Probench
                Emulation.
                >> Michael Kilimann <<

 - {m}  FIXED   68020+ code in 68000 version used.

(21-Apr-97)

 - {m}  FIXED   Assignwedge could not be disabled

 - {m}  OVERW   NewGadtools to improve centering of the gadget text
                >> Mario Cattaneo <<

 - {m}  FIXED   NewGadtools to show bold gadget texts
                >> Davide Bigazzi <<

(20-Apr-97)

 - {m}  FIXED   Automount problem

(19-Apr-97)

 - {s}  FIXED   Microdot slider problem.

 - {s}  FIXED   size problem for Reqtools requesters after restart.

 - {m}  ADDED   graphic system which should make the Powersave is now
                selectable.

(17-Apr-97)

 - {m}  ADDED   new function for the ScreenManager. Now it's possible, that
                the new screen gets the display mode from the first visible
                screen. This is very good to promote blanker screens.
                >> Mario Cattaneo <<
(14-Apr-97)

 - {m}  FIXED   wrong check of Automount devices

(12-Apr-97)

 - {s}  FIXED   ScreenManager bug

 - {s}  FIXED   ReqtoolsPatch bug

(11-Apr-97)

 - {m}  FIXED   ARPLibrary patch. Works now with TxEd !
                >> Jan-willem van Eys <<

 - {m}  FIXED   MCP installed two patches even though no function was activated

(10-Apr-97)

 - {s}  FIXED   wrong background colors with MCP-NoIconBorder patch

(08-Apr-97)

 - {m}  FIXED   some little bugs in ToolAlias

(06-Apr-97)

 - {s}  FIXED   Libsearch crash

(04-Apr-97)

 - {o}  FIXED   some Snap bugs

(01-Apr-97)

 - {m}  FIXED   Enforcer-Hit in the new ScreenPromotor.
                >> Ariel Magnum <<

(23-Mar-97)

 - {m}  FIXED   centering bug in NewGadTools (AB-Tools graphic was trashed)
                >> Peter Schulz <<

(17-Mar-97)

 - {o}  IMPRO   Snap now always works on 16/24 bit screens. Now it's a little
                problem with some colors in the background, but this will be
                fixed in the next time.

(15-Mar-97)

 - {m}  FIXED   Reqtools-Patch. To much removed from the program to kill
                the OneReq function.

(13-Mar-97)

 - {m}  REMOV   CenterScreens function. This function will be included in
                the new ScreenManager.

 - {m}  REMOV   OneReq function, because the _asl.library has a stack
                problem and this can't be changed from MCP.
                TitleClock window from the MCP-Prefs program crashed.

(09-Mar-97)

 - {m}  FIXED   stackproblem with Swazblanker modules

(08-Mar-97)

 - {m}  FIXED   placement of the underscore

(03-Mar-97)

 - {m}  ADDED   LockPens feature to ScreenManager

 - {s}  ADDED   Enter ASCII feature
                >> Mario 'padrino' Cattaneo <<

 - {s}  FIXED   bug in the 'Show Interface' function which runs the
                Prefsprogram.
                >> Mario 'padrino' Cattaneo <<

(01-Mar-97)

 - {m}  IMPRO   drawing of the gadget text
                >> Mario 'padrino' Cattaneo <<

 - {m}  ADDED   feature to increase the distance to the underscore
                >> Mario 'padrino' Cattaneo <<

(25-Feb-97)

 - {m}  FIXED   textlength in gadgets. Added a point to the end of the word.
                >> Mario 'padrino' Cattaneo <<

 - {m}  FIXED   look of the cycle gadget (same look as MUI)
                >> Mario 'padrino' Cattaneo <<

(21-Feb-97)

 - {m}  FIXED   possible crash if a program tries to open a window and no
                screen is available.
                >> Alexander Leidinger <<

 - {s}  FIXED   bug in CacheFont

(15-Feb-97)

 - {m}  FIXED   WBGauge now works with Scalos.

(02-Feb-97)

 - {m}  IMPRO   CycleToMenu. Now MCP installs only 2 patches on kick3.x and
                4 patches on kick2.x !! Additionally it works with the
                Picasso96Mode program from the Picasso96 software.
                Because of these changes the cyclegadget can flicker a little
                bit if you select a menu entry.
                >> Thanks for the Source from T.Abt and A.Kneer <<

(16-Jan-97)

 - {m}  FIXED   calculating the position of the popup menu
                >> Harry Sintonen <<

 - {m}  ADDED   new guru numbers to MCP.gurudat
                >> Harry Sintonen <<

(02-Jan-97)

 - {m}  FIXED   bug in ReqTimeOut. The Patternmatching routine from the
                operating system gives the false return value if the string
                contains a pipe '|'.

(22-Dec-96)

 - {s}  ADDED   Screenmanager and removed the old Promotor

(18-Dec-96)

 - {m}  FIXED   little bug in ReqToolsPatch
                >> Ralph Wermke <<

(16-Dec-96)

 - {m}  ADDED   NoFrag feature

(10-Dec-96)

 - {o}  ADDED   Snap feature

(29-Nov-96)

 - {m}  FIXED   little bug in the Reqtimeout. If a task makes a requester
                then the MatchPattern() call doesn't work and MCP has
                timed out the requester. Now all requesters which are made
                from a task will not be timed out.
                >> Harry Sintonen <<

****************************************************************************

@{b}MCP V1.22@{ub} --------- (22-Nov-96)

(22-Nov-96)

 - {m}  IMPRO   now MCP refreshes the window if a WBGauge was removed.

 - {m}  FIXED   MCPs version string.
                >> Claus Dilly <<

(12-Nov-96)

 - {m}  FIXED   possible crash if a program calls OpenWindowTagList() with
                no taglist. The editor Textra crashes sometimes.
                >> Chris Kerr <<

(08-Nov-96)

 - {m}  FIXED   crash if the prefsprogram called multiply via ShowInterface

 - {m}  ADDED   option to allow all Public-Screens for the Titleclock
                >> Martin Steigerwald <<

(05-Nov-96)

 - {m}  FIXED   possible crash if the device and unit from the SCSI-Eject
                command not given.

(04-Nov-96)

 - {m}  FIXED   Reqtimeout doesn't work sometimes. Hopefully the last bug.

(27-Oct-96)

 - {m}  FIXED   SysIhack which doesn't change the MUI and KingCON gadgets
                on Kick2.x.

 - {s}  FIXED   Hotkeys on Kick2.x.

 - {s}  FIXED   crash of NewGadTools on Kick2.x. Now the Number and Text
                gadgets will not be made on kick2.x.

(26-Oct-96)

 - {m}  FIXED   on Kick2.0 the mouse hotkeys doesn't work. The commodities
                library doesn't support the needed commands and hopefully
                it works a little bit better with this workaround.

(25-Oct-96)

 - {m}  FIXED   WBGauge doesn't work without NewGadtools

 - {m}  FIXED   on Kick2.x WBGauge could appear several times on the same
                window

 - {m}  FIXED   NewEdit crashed on Kick2.x

(24-Oct-96)

 - {m}  REMOV   SaveGIRPort function, because the new MagicMenu have
                included this.

(20-Oct-96)

 - {m}  ADDED   Hotkey to load and eject the SCSI-Media (CDROM, SyQuest)

(19-Oct-96)

 - {m}  FIXED   Finally removed the bug in ReqTimeout. It was very hard
                to find, because the bug doesn't appear with the english
                language.

 - {m}  FIXED   Two 68020 commands in the 68000 version.

(08-Oct-96)

 - {m}  REWRI   MCP now reads the last Gurunumber from the address $100
                on every start (also if you haven't activated 'Noguru' and
                'Alert-History'), but now it's not needed to read from this
                address if MCP restarts when you save the config.
                >> Daniel Weiss <<

(22-Sep-96)

 - {m}  ADDED   checking for Happy-ENV handler and mount ENV: if found.

 - {m}  FIXED   calculating of Dragbar-Gadget
                >> Daniel Weiss <<

(25-Aug-96)

 - {m}  ADDED   QuickDraw to make the drawing of vertical and horizontal
                lines a lot faster.
                >> Source from Harry Sintonen <<

 - {m}  IMPRO   System-Restore hotkey now updates the system clock.
                >> Jarda Pokorny <<

(19-Aug-96)

 - {m}  FIXED   WBAbout eats each time 300 Bytes of memory.
                >> Harry Sintonen <<

 - {m}  FIXED   LockPatch problem with some programs.

 - {m}  ADDED   RAMPatch to set the available memory to the size of the
                Ram-Disk.
                >> Source from Harry Sintonen <<

****************************************************************************

@{b}MCP V1.20@{ub} --------- (29-Jul-96)

(01-Aug-96)

 - {m}  FIXED   Quickformat-Protection was not off, if the complete
                Format-Protection was off.

(28-Jul-96)

 - {m}  ADDED   Aminet-version which checks the contents of a requester
                for the ReqTimeOut-Function, because it's not allowed
                to upload programs, which can be used to remove Shareware
                requesters.

(17-Jun-96)

 - {m}  FIXED   StackSwap usage, because of some crashes.

(16-Jun-96)

 - {m}  ADDED   NoQuickFormat option
                >> many thanks to Harry Sintonen for the source <<

(14-Jun-96)

 - {m}  FIXED   error in WBGauge fixed

(10-Jun-96)

 - {m}  FIXED   problem with screensmenu

(08-Jun-96)

 - {m}  FIXED   hopefully last bug in Powersaver.

(07-Jun-96)

 - {m}  FIXED   WBGauge doesn't work with some languages.

 - {m}  FIXED   check of processor doesn't work with the tooltypes
                >> Kevin Fairhurst <<

(06-Jun-96)

 - {m}  FIXED   now Cycle2Menu doesn't work if a requester is
                opened on this window.
                >> Jens Troeger <<

(05-Jun-96)

 - {m}  ADDED   three new types to show for the workbenchtitle.
                These types will show FastRam without VMM-Ram.
                >> Eka D. Durmin <<

(03-Jun-96)

 - {m}  IMPRO   the patternfield from the TitleClock now compares
                the pattern with the publicscreen name if the
                foremost screen is public.

(02-Jun-96)

 - {m}  FIXED   NewEdit paste doesn't work in the middle of a
                string.
                >> Dagfinn Olsen <<

(01-Jun-96)

 - {m}  FIXED   bug in 3D-borders. Now the borders will appear in
                more windows, too.

(27-May-96)

 - {m}  ADDED   NoIconBorder option to remove the borders from
                all Workbench icons.
                >> Stone-D (Laga M Hale) <<

(26-May-96)

 - {m}  FIXED   some problems of Cycle2Menu with locked windows

(23-May-96)

 - {m}  FIXED   now I have really found out what's wrong with
                the StackSwap() systemcall. In some programs
                (MultiFax,..) the last stackword is filled with
                'MANX' and the StackSwap() call from the
                operation system will write an other special word
                to this address.
                Now MCP has it's own StackSwap routine without
                writing the special word !!

(22-May-96)

 - {m}  FIXED   now the patternmatching bug is finally fixed.
                Because the patternmatching systemcall needs
                1500 bytes stack, we have made a new stack with
                StackSwap() and this call restores the stack
                sometimes wrong ;-(

 - {m}  ADDED   Hotkey to toggle the MemPatch-function
                >> Volker Remuss <<

(20-May-96)

 - {m}  FIXED   a possible crash if you have some patterns enabled

(11-May-96)

 - {m}  FIXED   SunPopToFront

 - {m}  FIXED   NewProp option now works with a ResetWB

(06-May-96)

 - {m}  ADDED   NewProp option for SysIHack, to give the propgad-
                gets in the WBWindow a better 3D look

(05-May-96)

 - {m}  FIXED   division by zero error in WBAbout

(02-May-96)

 - {m}  FIXED   a bug in the checking of the enable patterns for
                the functions.
                >> Leo Davidson <<

 - {m}  ADDED   new patches for mathpatch

 - {m}  FIXED   the routine which cuts the path from a task

(28-Apr-96)

 - {m}  IMPRO   with V39 the backfill-hook for the Cycle2Menu
                will be set to nobackfill, because it's faster.

(27-Apr-96)

 - {m}  FIXED   sometimes MCP produced Enforcer-Hits while restart
                itself.

(26-Apr-96)

 - {m}  FIXED   problems with underlines in some requesters
                >> Michael Kilimann <<

(24-Apr-96)

 - {m}  FIXED   problems with openwindow

(20-Apr-96)

 - {m}  FIXED   hopefully all problems with Cycle2Menu

(18-Apr-96)

 - {m}  ADDED   now the distance between the menu entries in the
                Cycle2Menu window are configurable.

(14-Apr-96)

 - {m}  FIXED   bug in promotor function (display-id)

(13-Apr-96)

 - {m}  FIXED   The Requtools-Patch make always two gadgets to
                an Autorequest requester, but also one gadget is
                allowed.
                >> Pablo d'Angelo <<

(12-Apr-96)

 - {m}  FIXED   the gap between the entries in Cycle2Menu is two
                points smaller now

 - {m}  FIXED   now Cycle2Menu isn't active on disabled gadgets
                >> Sven Ottemann <<

 - {m}  IMPRO   now MCP locks the input if Cycle2Menu is active
                >> Allan Odgaard <<

(07-Apr-96)

 - {m}  ADDED   now you can cancel the Cycle2Menu with the right
                mousebutton.

(06-Apr-96)

 - {m}  FIXED   bug with Cycle2Menu in conjunction with Intellifont.
                Because Intellifont uses a label array which isn't
                Null-terminated we have made a security check.

 - {m}  FIXED   Cycle2Menu. If the Menu doesn't fit on the screen
                then the Cycle2Menu doesn't popup.

(05-Apr-96)

 - {m}  ADDED   CycletoMenu Sticky option now allowes to use a
                popup menu or a normal menu at the same time.
                >> Michal L. Rybarski <<

(04-Apr-96)

 - {s}  FIXED   solid windowsizing didn't work on MC68000

 - {m}  FIXED   a bug caused by the system (hard to find ;-)
                Now Imploder V4.0 should work with MCP if you
                have switched on 'Move/Size full windows'.
                For programmers: MatchPatternNoCase crashes and
                we have to convert the string to upper case and use
                MatchPattern ;-(

 - {m}  IMPRO   MCP doesn't add the WBGauge if the window is
                currently opened, but now refreshes the window if
                MCP quits and the WBGauge will be removed.
                Also the window checking is improved now.

(03-Apr-96)

 - {s}  FIXED   WBAbout shows false CPU and FPU on MC68000

 - {m}  FIXED   Autoscroll, Interleaved and FixSize was set
                randomly in the promotor

(02-Apr-96)

 - {m}  FIXED   all problems with powersaver (I hope ;-)

 - {m}  FIXED   bug in Automount

 - {m}  FIXED   nasty bug in CycletoMenu (should be the last bug)

 - {m}  FIXED   bug in WBAbout

(01-Apr-96)

 - {m}  IMPRO   PatchMath don't need the patchieeesbpatch.library

(29-Mar-96)

 - {s}  FIXED   problems with solid move/size window

 - {s}  FIXED   TitleClock should be safer now

 - {s}  FIXED   crash if a patch couldn't be removed and you press retry

 - {s}  OVERW   whole MCP. Tables are now fully relative. Won nearly 3k.

(28-Mar-96)

 - {s}  FIXED   Patternmatching didn't filters the path right

(22-Mar-96)

 - {ms} ADDED   CycleToMenu

(21-Mar-96)

 - {m}  ADDED   AlertTimeout

(20-Mar-96)

 - {s}  OVERW   MCP restart is now safer

(18-Mar-96)

 - {s}  ADDED   finally finished work on NewGadtools

(16-Mar-96)

 - {m}  ADDED   PatchMath

 - {m}  ADDED   Enable or disable tasks for the blanker

(13-Mar-96)

 - {m}  ADDED   AutoMount

 - {m}  ADDED   NoBootWrite to the Formatprotection

(12-Mar-96)

 - {m}  ADDED   WBAbout

 - {m}  FIXED   some bugs in ReqToolsPatch and MemPatch.

(09-Mar-96)

 - {m}  ADDED   Hotkeys to start all three parts of the powersaver

 - {m}  ADDED   NoDisplayBeep

 - {m}  ADDED   Trackdisk settings for the 4 floppy drives and
                included NoClick to this settings

(08-Mar-96)

 - {m}  FIXED   problems if you call MCPPrefs from Exchange

(04-Mar-96)

 - {ms} ADDED   patch for the ugly Windowtitle gadgets for MUI and
                KingCON-Iconify

(22-Feb-96)

 - {m}  ADDED   Exclusion and Inclusion of specified tasks or
                screens for SunMouse, SunPop2Front, TitleClock,
                MoveWindow and SizeWindow features

(21-Feb-96)

 - {m}  ADDED   MCPASSIGN Tooltype
                >> Michael Kilimann <<

(20-Feb-96)

 - {m}  FIXED   FullWindowSizing in one direction

 - {m}  IMPRO   patchsystem and memoryallocation

(04-Feb-96)

 - {m}  FIXED   Powersaver now works correctly with CybergraphX on
                Amigascreens.

 - {m}  FIXED   MCP now supports new Swazblanker
                (not supported are the versions 2.40 and 2.41)

****************************************************************************

@{b}MCP V1.10@{ub} --------- (03-Feb-96)

(03-Feb-96)

 - {s}  FIXED   Hotkey Mouserelease problem.

(02-Feb-96)

 - {s}  FIXED   NewEdit problems with CygnusEd.
                >> Vesa Halttunen <<

 - {s}  FIXED   NewEdit Copy/Paste will now only work with iffparse
                library V39 or higher.

 - {s}  FIXED   PowerSaver for CyberGraphX.

 - {s}  FIXED   SunMouse didn't work. This was a simple type error.
                >> Giovanni Addabbo <<

 - {s}  FIXED   MCP lock if the blanker couldn't been loaded.

 - {s}  FIXED   AppChange. Filtering out the path now. Better WB-start check.

 - {s}  FIXED   little path-problems in execute-command.

 - {s}  OVERW   automatic MemPatch disabling on Amiga-screens.

(27-Jan-96)

 - {s}  FIXED   problems with the Shift-Hotkey
                >> Bussi <<

(25-Jan-96)

 - {s}  ADDED   path-copy to 'Execute-Command' hotkey

(24-Jan-96)

 - {s}  REMOV   OCS-Powersaver

(22-Jan-96)

 - {m}  FIXED   MCP-ToolTypes now changed back if the program quits and a
                new program is loaded

 - {m}  FIXED   problems with the 'RestoreSystem'-Hotkey

(21-Jan-96)

 - {s}  IMPRO   NewEdit. New options:
                 - ramiga l - lower cases
                 - ramiga shift l - uppercase
                 - ramiga v - is now paste with insert
                 - ramiga shift v - paste with clear
                 - lamiga key - original ramiga key


 - {s}  FIXED   MCP uses now always the usa keymap for hotkey-inits.

(20-Jan-96)

 - {s}  FIXED   ZipWindow hotkey. Now checks for Window-HasZoom.

 - {s}  FIXED   ClickToBack and CycleWindow FrontToBack. Checks now for
                Window-Depthgadget.

 - {v}  OVERW   mcpsupport.library LoadFile routine. More future compatible
                now.

(19-Jan-96)

 - {m}  FIXED   Dimmer. Works now fine on Kick 2.x.

(18-Jan-96)

 - {s}  FIXED   PropHack. It works now right with YACDP and OctaMed. This
                Programs doesn't use the slider real systemconform.

 - {s}  FIXED   PROGDIR: problem in LibSearch.


(15-Jan-96)

 - {m}  REWRI   IRQ Timing routine.

(14-Jan-96)

 - {m}  ADDED   MCP disables the 'MemoryPatch' for the task which
                opens an AmigaScreen.

(13-Jan-96)

 - {s}  ADDED   FastRom for 68030 and 68851 (not tested).

 - {m}  ADDED   FastRom for 68040/68060.

(12-Jan-96)

 - {m}  REWRI   IRQ-Routine. Now messages instead of signals used.

(10-Jan-96)

 - {s}  FIXED   Hotkey recognition finally.

(09-Jan-96)

 - {s}  FIXED   PointerBlanker.

(08-Jan-96)

 - {s}  FIXED   ReqTimeOut. It doesn't know the default-title right.

 - {s}  FIXED   Enforcerhit in AssignWedge.

 - {s}  FIXED   OpenWindow patch. It works now fine with Ceds JumpLine.

 - {s}  FIXED   bad bug in 68000 version.

(07-Jan-96)

 - {v}  OVERW   Lib and Font search.

(06-Jan-96)

 - {s}  FIXED   Diskinsert, Diskremove and Timer Hotkeys doesn't work
                with "Execute command"
(05-Jan-96)

 - {m}  FIXED   Power Saver.

(04-Jan-96)

 - {s}  FIXED   problems with pointerblanker and 16 color pointer.
                >> Ramses <<
(03-Jan-95)

 - {s}  ADDED   Copy (RAMIGA c) to Clipboard and Paste (RAMIGA v) to
                NewEdit.

 - {m}  FIXED   Hotkeys will be disabled if a menu is opened.
                >> Frank Toepper <<

(02-Jan-96)

 - {s}  REWRI   Startup code. MCP could now better removed if Executive
                is installed.

(01-Jan-96)

 - {s}  ADDED   Audio-filter in Processor Page.

 - {s}  FIXED   little problems with new hotkeys.

(30-Dec-95)

 - {m}  ADDED   'MCPFLUSH' and 'MCPNOCACHES' ToolTypes

(29-Dec-95)

 - {m}  FIXED   'ToolTypes' now only switches the specified cache off and
                doesn't switch all other caches on.

 - {m}  ADDED   all new 68060-Cache Tooltypes.

 - {m}  ADDED   full 68060 Processor support (BranchCache, SuperScalar,
                StoreBuffer, HalfInstrCache, HalfDataCache, WriteAllocate
                and DisableFPU)

(28-Dec-95)

 - {m}  ADDED   Powermanagement. MCP supports all 3 parts of the DPMS and
                it's possible to give every part a specified time.

 - {m}  ADDED   Garshneblanker now returns to a black screen if no time is
                left.

 - {m}  FIXED   MoveWindow and Sizewindow will check every time if
                the window is currently active.
                >> Ralph Wermke, Frank Toepper <<

(23-Dec-95)

 - {m}  OVERW   Dimmerroutine. Now the Dimmdepth must be given in
                percent and the Dimmer doesn't dimm HAM-Screens.

(20-Dec-95)

 - {s}  FIXED   CenterScreens.

(15-Dec-95)

 - {s}  REWRI   Hotkey detection routine.

(12-Dec-95)

 - {s}  FIXED   Force NewLook menus.

 - {s}  FIXED   little GFX error in left and right arrow of SysIHack.

(11-Dec-95)

 - {s}  FIXED   SysIHack works now on Kickstart 2.x.

 - {s}  FIXED   CapsShift. It works now correctly.

 - {s}  FIXED   Hold X and Hold Y exchanged.

(10-Dec-95)

 - {s}  FIXED   Processor-Option. Prefs-reading didn't work right. All
                options are now only setable except VBR to Fast. FastGary is
                now compatible to the 68040.

(09-Dec-95)

 - {s}  OVERW   checking of AssignWedge. Works now with YourFault. No more
                need of locale.library.

(08-Dec-95)

 - {s}  FIXED   bad bug on OpenWindowTags patch. It causes a crash on 68000
                and NewLookMenus was always on.

(03-Dec-95)
 - {m}  FIXED   Randomroutine for Blanker

(29-Nov-95)

 - {s}  FIXED   'ZipWindow' hotkey. Works now with WB-Prefsprograms.

(28-Nov-95)

 - {s}  ADDED   MCPNOMEMPATCH tooltype.

(27-Nov-95)

 - {s}  FIXED   'Quicklayers'. It works now fine with the DOpus viewer :)

(26-Nov-95)

 - {s}  FIXED   usage of "`" Hotkey.

 - {s}  ADDED   "SHIFT" and "ALT" hotkeys.

(25-Nov-95)

 - {s}  ADDED   'SysIHack'

(24-Nov-95)

 - {m}  OVERW   Checkroutine for 'Full Windowmoving' and 'Full Windowsizing'
